        "## Find shortest paths between all pairs of vertices using Floyd Warshall algorithm."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "QGMOsFLdhP86"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#Understand all pairs shortest path problem. Implement dynamic programming approach in Python.\n",
        "\n",
        "* Given a weighted graph with positive or negative edge weights, find\n",
        "shortest distances between every pair of vertices."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "hBh39xfUhbFc"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Theory\n",
        "Floyd Warshall algorithm computes shortest paths between all pairs of nodes. It updates the distance matrix by checking if a shorter path exists through an intermediate vertex. Works with negative weights but fails with negative cycles.\n",
        "\n",
        "Algorithm\n",
        "1. Represent graph using distance matrix.\n",
        "2. Initialize matrix with given weights.\n",
        "3. Set distance of node to itself as 0.\n",
        "4. For each intermediate vertex k\n",
        "5. Update distance[i][j] = min(distance[i][j], distance[i][k] + distance[k][j])\n",
        "6. Repeat for all vertices"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "L_1NZKDSiC5U"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def floyd_warshall(graph):\n",
        "\n",
        "    n = len(graph)\n",
        "\n",
        "    dist = []\n",
        "    next_node = [] # Added next_node for path reconstruction\n",
        "    for i in range(n):\n",
        "        dist.append(graph[i][:])\n",
        "        next_node.append([j for j in range(n)]) # Initialize next_node[i][j] to j\n",
        "\n",
        "    for k in range(n):\n",
        "        for i in range(n):\n",
        "            for j in range(n):\n",
        "                # Check if path through k is shorter\n",
        "                if dist[i][k] != float('inf') and dist[k][j] != float('inf') and dist[i][k] + dist[k][j] < dist[i][j]:\n",
        "                    dist[i][j] = dist[i][k] + dist[k][j]\n",
        "                    next_node[i][j] = next_node[i][k] # Update next_node to pass through k\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Detect negative cycles by checking if distance from a node to itself is negative\n",
        "    # This specific detection is actually done in a separate function,\n",
        "    # but the presence of negative cycles can make the 'dist' matrix inaccurate for paths.\n",
        "\n",
        "    return dist, next_node # Return both dist and next_node"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "acklfR7JiYRw"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
